The atmosphere is neat, and it has a large patio that looks promising on a cool fall night.
The service was fine, and the food was fine, but for almost $70 on a week night it's a bit overpriced.
Most of the entrees are almost $20 a piece, but it's not like this place is super upscale or fancy....I think it needs to decide what it wants to be.....good ole Mexican or Mexican upscale.
Right now it is a weird hybrid, and so you don't leave satisfied....or at least I expected good ole Mexican but left with a steakhouse bill!
I would give it another shot, though.

