The dish describes veggies in the pasta, but little was seen.
The drinks were ok, but tasted like Sprite was added to the margaritas.
We had enough of the food and got the cake to go, which actually was the best part we ate the next day.
It was 100 degrees that night, and we ate inside....SUFFER and eat outside...the ambiance is much better (fountain and lights) than inside (dim and plain).
The service was great (the reason for 2 stars)!!!!
But too bad the food/drinks couldn't match :(.
I felt the experience wasn't worth the $44, and could've got better tex/mex at a hole in the wall place somewhere else in Scottsdale.
